<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="un2013k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un2" href="#un2013">UN2: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un2all.htm#un2013k"> (VI.D.7) 13(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> morganatic marriage unknown in Hungary. If F.F. becomes K of H wife queen her rank</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">THE AUSTRO-HUNGARIAN SUCCESSION. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <br>An issue of considerable interest was unexpectedly raised in the Hungarian Chamber by a prominent member, M. Geza Polonyi. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> the Hungarian Independence party had taken up the standpoint that since <mark>morganatic marriages were unknown to Hungarian law</mark> the marriage of the heir-apparent was in every respect juridically valid in Hungary. Consequently the issue of the marriage was, in the opinion of the Independence party, entitled to succeed to the throne. <mark>Should the Archduke Franz Ferdinand ascend the Hungarian throne his consosrt would under Hungarian law and also according to the view prevalent in Hungarian society be regarded as Queen</mark>. <small> <a name="TT16jun04" href="/udra/udex.htm#tt16jun04"><cite title="source">The Times</cite></a> (London, 16 June 1904), 5/6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c16242g" href="../../../f/ff/fnbs/c16all.htm#c16242g">VI.C.16:242(g)</a>, <a name="c16243a" href="../../../f/ff/fnbs/c16all.htm#c16243a">VI.C.16:243(a)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
